		<h2>SPOJ Problem Set (classical)</h2>
				<h1>10537. Edit Distance Again</h1>
		<h2>Problem code: EDIT</h2>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table>

<p align="justify">
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div id="_mcePaste" style="position: absolute; left: -10000px; top: 0px; width: 1px; height: 1px; overflow-x: hidden; overflow-y: hidden;">As any experienced programmer must know the famous problem of "Edit Distance", however this</div>
<div id="_mcePaste" style="position: absolute; left: -10000px; top: 0px; width: 1px; height: 1px; overflow-x: hidden; overflow-y: hidden;">problem is considered an &ldquo;alternating chain&rdquo; if you have alternately made case sensitive.</div>
<div id="_mcePaste" style="position: absolute; left: -10000px; top: 0px; width: 1px; height: 1px; overflow-x: hidden; overflow-y: hidden;">Example:</div>
<div id="_mcePaste" style="position: absolute; left: -10000px; top: 0px; width: 1px; height: 1px; overflow-x: hidden; overflow-y: hidden;">"AaAaAbB" "B" "a" "aBaCdEf"</div>
<div id="_mcePaste" style="position: absolute; left: -10000px; top: 0px; width: 1px; height: 1px; overflow-x: hidden; overflow-y: hidden;">Alternating chains are considered in our problem.</div>
<div id="_mcePaste" style="position: absolute; left: -10000px; top: 0px; width: 1px; height: 1px; overflow-x: hidden; overflow-y: hidden;">We only have one operation that is permitted in exchange for a lower or upper case Latin letter.</div>
<div id="_mcePaste" style="position: absolute; left: -10000px; top: 0px; width: 1px; height: 1px; overflow-x: hidden; overflow-y: hidden;">Given a string giving the minimum number of changes to be considered an alternating chain.</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>As any experienced programmer must know the famous problem of "Edit Distance", however this</p>
<p>problem is considered an &ldquo;alternating chain&rdquo; if you have alternately made case sensitive.</p>
<p>Example:</p>
<p>"AaAaAbB" "B" "a" "aBaCdEf"</p>
<p>Alternating chains are considered in our problem.</p>
<p>We only have one operation that is permitted in exchange for a lower or upper case Latin letter.</p>
<p>Given a string giving the minimum number of changes to be considered an alternating chain.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Input</h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>A string with no spaces line containing only uppercase and lowercase letters, one for each line of</p>
<p>maximum length 10 ^ 3 until end of file</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Output</h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>For each line print the minimum number of changes to the chain is a "chain alternately"</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Example</h3>
<pre><strong>Input:</strong>
AaAaB
ABaa
a

<strong>Output:</strong>
0
2
0</pre>

